  "text": "Cell viability was monitored using Cell Counting Kit-8 (CCK-8) (Dojindo Laboratories) as described previously [CITATION_1] . In brief, after transfection, cells were treated with a gradient concentration of gemcitabine (GEMZAR, Eli Lilly and Company) for 72 h. Then, after incubation with CCK-8 for 1.5 h, the absorbance was measured at 450 nm (ELx808, BioTek, USA); IC50 values referring to the gemcitabine concentration were calculated using Graph-Pad Prism 6.01 software.",
